<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 03 at 1:18PM MDT  by NWS Missoula</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Silver Bow
County through 145 PM MDT...
At 117 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northeast of Divide, or 10 miles southwest of Butte, moving
northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail and heavy rainfall.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Butte, Janney, and Newcomb.
This includes Interstate 90 between mile markers 222 and 231.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
